    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CRC32 lookup table initialization and calculation in PHY coding\n\n### Summary\nThe CRC32 functions in the PHY coding module had two critical issues that prevented proper operation. First, the `crc32_init_lut` function was declared in the header but never implemented, causing link-time errors when users attempted to initialize CRC32 lookup tables. Second, the `crc32_calc_lut` inline function used an inconsistent calculation pattern that didn't match the established conventions in the codebase.\n\nThis fix implements the missing `crc32_init_lut` function and corrects the calculation pattern in `crc32_calc_lut` to align with other CRC implementations. Additionally, a complete CRC32 processing function `crc32` was added to provide a built-in table-driven implementation similar to the existing CRC16/CRC24 functions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/crc.h`: Fixed calculation pattern in `crc32_calc_lut` and added declaration for `crc32` function.\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/crc_byte.c`: Implemented `crc32_init_lut` function, added `crc32` table-driven function, and integrated CRC32 table initialization into `crcTableInit`.\n\nWhen calling `crc32_calc_lut()` with an uninitialized lookup table, the behavior was undefined due to missing table initialization. After this fix, users can properly initialize CRC32 lookup tables using `crc32_init_lut(0x04C11DB7, lut)` before calling `crc32_calc_lut()`.\n\n"
}